 Curve:\n\nTime (months) | Survival Probability\n--------------|---------------------\n10            | 0.98\n20            | 0.98 * 0.9796 ≈ 0.960\n30            | 0.960 * 0.9375 ≈ 0.900\n40            | 0.900 * 0.9556 ≈ 0.860\n45            | 0.860 * 0.9767 ≈ 0.840\n50            | 0.840 * 0.9762 ≈ 0.820\n60            | 0.820 * 0.9268 ≈ 0.760\n65            | 0.760 * 0.9737 ≈ 0.740\n70            | 0.740 * 0.9459 ≈ 0.700\n80            | 0.700 * 0.8857 ≈ 0.620\n85            | 0.620 * 0.9032 ≈ 0.560\n90            | 0.560 * 0.9286 ≈ 0.520\n95            | 0.520 * 0.9615 ≈ 0.500\n100           | 0.500 * 0.92 = 0.460\n105           | 0.460 * 0.9565 ≈ 0.440\n110           | 0.440 * 0.9091 ≈ 0.400\n115           | 0.400 * 0.95 = 0.380\n120           | 0.380 * 0.8947 ≈ 0.340\n125           | 0.340 * 0.8235 ≈ 0.280\n130           | 0.280 * 0.9286 ≈ 0.260\n135           | 0.260 * 0.8462 ≈ 0.220\n140           | 0.220 * 0.8182 ≈ 0.180\n145           | 0.180 * 0.8889 ≈ 0.160\n150           | 0.160 * 0.875 = 0.140\n155           | 0.140 * 0.7143 ≈ 0.100\n160           | 0.100 * 0.6 = 0.060\n165           | 0.060 * 0.6667 ≈ 0.040\n170           | 0.040 * 0 = 0\n\nThe median survival time is the time at which the survival probability is 0.5, which is approximately 95 months.\n\nThe survival rate at 2 years (24 months) can be found by interpolating between the survival probabilities at 20 and 30 months. \n\nSurvival rate at 24 months ≈ (0.960 + 0.900) / 2 ≈ 0.930\n\nSo, the survival rate at 2 years is approximately 93%."
